title: Sepia saya
text:
Sepia saya is a species of <a href="cuttlefish">cuttlefish</a> known only from its <a href="type%20locality%20%28biology%29">type locality</a> in the southwestern <a href="Indian%20Ocean">Indian Ocean</a>. It lives at depths of 87 to 117 m.
"Sepia saya" grows to a <a href="mantle%20%28mollusc%29">mantle</a> length of 90 mm.
The <a href="type%20specimen">type specimen</a> was collected near the <a href="Saya-de-Malha%20Bank">Saya-de-Malha Bank</a> in the <a href="Indian%20Ocean">Indian Ocean</a> ( to ). It is deposited at the <a href="Zoological%20Museum%20of%20the%20Zoological%20Institute%20of%20the%20Russian%20Academy%20of%20Sciences">Zoological Museum in Moscow</a>.
